Data visualsation project using Bike trips (San Francisco)¶

by (Ellen)¶

This project explores bike trips for a bike sharing platform using collated from 174363 (after data wrangling) total bike trips of various durations.

This Jupyter Notebook (ProjectBikes_Part1.ipynb and Project_Bikes_Part1.html) will explore the data using exploratory data analysis (EDA). The cleaned exported data from this workbook (bikes_clean_master.csv) will be used to create explantory visualization in the second Jupyter Notebook (Project_Bikes_Part2.ipynb and Project_Bikes_Part2.html). Finally a slide deck will be created using the visualizations of the second Jupyter Notebook.

Assessment¶

Several columns contain null values including

  • start_station_id
  • start_station_name
  • end_station_id
  • end_station_name
  • member_birth_year
  • member_gener

Both columns start_time and end_time need to be in datetime format for visualisations later

Wrangling¶

Define¶

Remove rows where no gender is labelled (and birth year by proxy)

Code¶

In [185]:
bikes_clean = bikes_clean[bikes_clean['member_gender'].isnull() == False]
# Remove rows where no gender is labelled
# Removing this column of gender also removes the 8265 null labels for birth year

What is the structure of the dataset?¶

  • 175952 bike trips on a bike sharing service in a city. The data set contains information such as
  • trip duration: how long the trip took (in seconds). I've added a column for minutes and hours.
  • start time and end time: the start and end time and date for each trip
  • stations_id: start/end station,
  • location (latitude/longitude): the location of the bike station
  • gender: gender of user
  • user type: whether a subscriber or a pay as you go customer
  • bikes_id: unique id of bike

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in the dataset?¶

  • Time of rental (using time date)
  • Day of rental (are more bikes used on weekends or weekdays)
  • Gender use of bikes
  • General length of bike rentals

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

  • Duration columns: (I added extra columns for duration in minutes and hours
  • Gender column: Rows with no gender column were removed
  • Day of rental: I created a new coulmn to extract day of bike rental

Their useage does not decrease with the weekend.

This is interesting as subscribers use this service less on weekends, but still pay for it. Let's explore this visual a bit more with days of week and users.

Wow, so this is neat, so while subscribers use the service less on weekends, their actual trip durations actually increase during the weekend. This is also seen with customers. However overall their trip lengths are shorter.

Generally for the different genders, the trip duration also increases. However, males tend to have longer trips.
